## Batch processing and frontend insertion
 
Processing is batch, not streaming. The whole receipt resolves before the frontend receives anything. Total processing time for a typical grocery receipt is 3–6 seconds.
 
- Receipt image is uploaded via `POST /upload/receipt`
- Pipeline runs on each OCR line sequentially, collects all resolved canonical names into an array
- Single JSON response returned to frontend: `extracted_items[]`, `unresolved[]`, `warnings[]`
- Frontend insertion treats resolved items identically to manually typed pantry entries — same dictionary validation, same canonical name, same UI treatment
- `unresolved[]` is surfaced to the user as a review list for optional manual addition
- Manual pantry entry runs through the same dictionary matching layer — fuzzy matching catches typos like `chiken brest` and resolves to `chicken breast` before writing
