## Build order
 
The following sequence minimizes over-development and produces a testable result at each step before proceeding.
 
- Dictionary matching against cached MealDB list — validates the truth layer before anything else is built
- Token cleaning — self-contained, testable with hardcoded receipt strings, no external dependencies
- Abbreviation expansion table — seed with LLM call, wire lookup into pipeline after cleaning is confirmed working
- OCR integration — Google Cloud Vision returns raw lines, pipeline already handles the rest
- Batch endpoint — `POST /upload/receipt` wiring OCR output through the pipeline to JSON response
- Frontend receipt upload — file input triggering the endpoint, existing pantry insertion logic handles the response
- GLM fallback — built last, after real receipt failures reveal what actually escapes the main path